examples.en: He sighed with relief when he saw that he passed the test.
He sighed but did not awaken.
I may never see my old home again, she sighed.
'Don't turn on the waterworks,' he sighed.
Mother clicked her tongue (=made a short sound to show disapproval) and sighed.
The wind sighed in the trees.
Emilia sighed for her lost youth.
The wind sighed through the trees.
He sighed with despair at the thought of all the opportunities he had missed.
Frankie stared out of the window and sighed deeply.
I'll stop off and get us a sandwich, said Matthew. Tony, a fastidious eater, sighed.
